<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,327]" pageId="6" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="20">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Enderlein, 1926" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1926" box="[792,1118,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Systropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excisus">
<emphasis box="[792,905,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="20">S. excisus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Enderlein" box="[920,1110,152,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="20" refString="Enderlein, G. (1926) Zur Kenntnis der Bombyliiden-Subfamilie Systropodinae (Dipt.). Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 43, 69 - 92." type="journal article" year="1926">
Enderlein, 
<number box="[1050,1110,152,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="20" value="1926.0">1926</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1188,1258,152,178]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="20">China</collectingCountry>
(Gangdong) in having similar antennal coloration, but it can be separated from the latter by the apex of the hind tibia yellow and the metasternum yellow with two wide black stripes joined anteriorly. In 
<taxonomicName box="[1069,1184,226,251]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Systropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excisus">
<emphasis box="[1069,1184,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="20">S. excisus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the apex of the hind tibia is black; the metasternum is yellow with two wide black stripes not joined anteriorly (
<bibRefCitation author="Nagatomi" pageId="6" pageNumber="20" refString="Nagatomi, A., Liu, N. W., Tamaki, N. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L. (1991) The genus Systropus from Japan, Korea, Taiwan and Thailand (Diptera, Bombyliidae). South Pacific Study, 12 (1), 23 - 112." type="journal article" year="1991">
Nagatomi 
<emphasis box="[1375,1436,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[151,214,301,327]" pageId="6" pageNumber="20" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
